name: CSS
jsDoc: Holds useful CSS-related methods. No object with this interface are implemented: it contains only static methods and therefore is a utilitarian interface.

name: dispatchEvent
jsDoc: Dispatches a synthetic event event to target and returns true if either event's cancelable attribute value is false or its preventDefault() method was not invoked, and false otherwise.

name: onabort
jsDoc:
Fires when the user aborts the download.
@param ev The event.

name: onblur
jsDoc:
Fires when the object loses the input focus.
@param ev The focus event.

name: oncanplay
jsDoc:
Occurs when playback is possible, but would require further buffering.
@param ev The event.

name: onchange
jsDoc:
Fires when the contents of the object or selection have changed.
@param ev The event.

name: onclick
jsDoc:
Fires when the user clicks the left mouse button on the object
@param ev The mouse event.

name: oncontextmenu
jsDoc:
Fires when the user clicks the right mouse button in the client area, opening the context menu.
@param ev The mouse event.

name: ondblclick
jsDoc:
Fires when the user double-clicks the object.
@param ev The mouse event.

name: ondrag
jsDoc:
Fires on the source object continuously during a drag operation.
@param ev The event.

name: ondragend
jsDoc:
Fires on the source object when the user releases the mouse at the close of a drag operation.
@param ev The event.

name: ondragenter
jsDoc:
Fires on the target element when the user drags the object to a valid drop target.
@param ev The drag event.

name: ondragleave
jsDoc:
Fires on the target object when the user moves the mouse out of a valid drop target during a drag operation.
@param ev The drag event.

name: ondragover
jsDoc:
Fires on the target element continuously while the user drags the object over a valid drop target.
@param ev The event.

name: ondragstart
jsDoc:
Fires on the source object when the user starts to drag a text selection or selected object.
@param ev The event.

name: ondurationchange
jsDoc:
Occurs when the duration attribute is updated.
@param ev The event.

name: onemptied
jsDoc:
Occurs when the media element is reset to its initial state.
@param ev The event.

name: onended
jsDoc:
Occurs when the end of playback is reached.
@param ev The event

name: onerror
jsDoc:
Fires when an error occurs during object loading.
@param ev The event.

name: onfocus
jsDoc:
Fires when the object receives focus.
@param ev The event.

name: onkeydown
jsDoc:
Fires when the user presses a key.
@param ev The keyboard event

name: onkeypress
jsDoc:
Fires when the user presses an alphanumeric key.
@param ev The event.

name: onkeyup
jsDoc:
Fires when the user releases a key.
@param ev The keyboard event

name: onload
jsDoc:
Fires immediately after the browser loads the object.
@param ev The event.

name: onloadeddata
jsDoc:
Occurs when media data is loaded at the current playback position.
@param ev The event.

name: onloadedmetadata
jsDoc:
Occurs when the duration and dimensions of the media have been determined.
@param ev The event.

name: onloadstart
jsDoc:
Occurs when Internet Explorer begins looking for media data.
@param ev The event.

name: onmousedown
jsDoc:
Fires when the user clicks the object with either mouse button.
@param ev The mouse event.

name: onmousemove
jsDoc:
Fires when the user moves the mouse over the object.
@param ev The mouse event.

name: onmouseout
jsDoc:
Fires when the user moves the mouse pointer outside the boundaries of the object.
@param ev The mouse event.

name: onmouseover
jsDoc:
Fires when the user moves the mouse pointer into the object.
@param ev The mouse event.

name: onmouseup
jsDoc:
Fires when the user releases a mouse button while the mouse is over the object.
@param ev The mouse event.

name: onpause
jsDoc:
Occurs when playback is paused.
@param ev The event.

name: onplay
jsDoc:
Occurs when the play method is requested.
@param ev The event.

name: onplaying
jsDoc:
Occurs when the audio or video has started playing.
@param ev The event.

name: onprogress
jsDoc:
Occurs to indicate progress while downloading media data.
@param ev The event.

name: onratechange
jsDoc:
Occurs when the playback rate is increased or decreased.
@param ev The event.

name: onreset
jsDoc:
Fires when the user resets a form.
@param ev The event.

name: onscroll
jsDoc:
Fires when the user repositions the scroll box in the scroll bar on the object.
@param ev The event.

name: onseeked
jsDoc:
Occurs when the seek operation ends.
@param ev The event.

name: onseeking
jsDoc:
Occurs when the current playback position is moved.
@param ev The event.

name: onselect
jsDoc:
Fires when the current selection changes.
@param ev The event.

name: onstalled
jsDoc:
Occurs when the download has stopped.
@param ev The event.

name: onsuspend
jsDoc:
Occurs if the load operation has been intentionally halted.
@param ev The event.

name: ontimeupdate
jsDoc:
Occurs to indicate the current playback position.
@param ev The event.

name: onvolumechange
jsDoc:
Occurs when the volume is changed, or playback is muted or unmuted.
@param ev The event.

name: onwaiting
jsDoc:
Occurs when playback stops because the next frame of a video resource is not available.
@param ev The event.
